Ang and Bekaert (1999) assume Markov‐switching returns to compute their optimal portfolio weights versus ignoring this information and solving a myopic (one‐period) expected utility calculation. They assume power utility and aT‐period horizon with all proceeds reinvested. Campbell and Viceira (1999) evaluate suboptimal strategies, in the context of multiperiod Epstein‐Zin utility functions, by computing the percentage loss of the optimal value function, that is,
